race.comment: BLUE HAWAIIAN (12) resumes off a jumpout win. She was racing consistently well last time in, including winning her maiden over this track and distance by nearly five lengths, taking on a couple of handy races thereafter. This looks a nice race for her down in the weights from a good draw. MR ASSERTIVE (1) dropped back slightly in grade at Geelong last time out and proved far too good, scoring by 2.75 lengths. This is another good option and he'll take plenty of catching. ESCARPA (10) continues to race very well since a fresh win having not missed the placings in four subsequent runs. She'll need a bit of luck from the inside gate but can be rattling home if the breaks come. BOLD RESPONSE (9) is speedy and will give a sight if left alone.
